<br>
I'm an MMO veteran going way back to text MUD/MMO pre-UO days.  I've beta tested many of the current crop.  I already knew PvP was borked in SWG, but I'm very unPvP oriented and decided to give SWG a try anyway despite not likeing Star Wars.  Just so my background is clear.   <br>
<br>
After going CH, adding BE .. then reading Star Wars background and thinking &quot;Ooo DE must be good&quot;, then looking at DE and running back to CH/BE:  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I decided to stick out the initial MMO phase by levelling up a second CH/BE since I can't change race and wanted to try, of all things, .. armor.<br>
<br>
Some folks I'd met quit the game.  Three fourths of my friends list is gone.  Others are considering it.  Many log in less.  But, school started and the &quot;Lets go look at the new MMO!&quot; crowd just got done with thier free months.   I wasn't overly worried.  <br>
<br>
Then I started reading the forums more for updates on bugs that well bugged me, and nerf announcements so I could adjust my skills as I brought up the new char as needed.   There were flame fests and porting wars over nerfs and &quot;why did you ignore me while you nerfed them&quot; wars.  Some post war/fests were ignored.  Others, like the one in our CH forum, clearly had a dev come in and try to do damage control.  OK, seems par for a rough start up.<br>
<br>
Then today I really began to wonder.  There were at least two posts.  One had some CSR chat log that I wasn't able to read, not sure on it.  Another was a post by one of the class correspondents who was either quitting the game or the post - I'm not sure.  It seemed calm, but had the word wrap bug in my browser.  So, I hit refresh.<br>
<br>
Instead of the post I got a message that the post had been deleted.  One reply, right below was a short messge along the lines of - you did a good job and thanks for the effort.  So no flame fest either.  Another post I had just finished reading compared some of the current actions of the SWG team to post-release actions of the AC2 team.  It was also calm and flame free.  Making a few suggestions.  When I looked at the index, it too was deleted.  In the time it took me to hit the top 4 pages (things drop so fast have to be sure they are gone not just off the page) - a couple of threads about the heavy moderation appeared.  They were deleted every refresh.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong.  I've even posted in a couple of flame fests with a short &quot;this is out of hand, hope its locked soon&quot; post.   I'm all for constructive moderation - thats good for the community.<br>
<br>
What I just saw wasn't constructive.  It was the same paniced locking I saw in AC2 and AO - post release when the realization started hitting the non-beta folks and patience with bugs was gone.  They paniced and locked down boards too.  SWG hasn't announced a lock down.  But thats effectively what they are doing.  And they aren't locking .. they are DELETING.  Quickly.  <br>
<br>
Thats the first thing I've seen that does make me wonder about the long term viability of sticking it out in this game.<br>
<br>
Hmmmm.<br>
